<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Atom specification says a feed MUST have an author element, whether at the entry level or at the feed level. Documentation of Zend_Feed::importArray() says:
'author'      =&gt; 'author/publisher of the feed', //optional
but if author is not specified in every entry, the resulting feed is not valid. Nowadays  element is not supported (but there's a patch in bug ZF-5611), so:
- include that patch and specify 'required' on $array['entries'][$i]['author']
- or correct docs and specify 'required' on $array['author']</p>

